# Clerk Authentication & Data Security

All authentication is handled by Clerk. Users must ONLY be able to access their own data and NEVER access data belonging to other users.

## Required Authentication Patterns

### ✅ ALWAYS Get Current User
```typescript
import { auth, currentUser } from '@clerk/nextjs';

// API Routes
export async function GET() {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) {
    return new Response('Unauthorized', { status: 401 });
  }
  // ... use userId for data filtering
}

// Server Actions
export async function createDeck(data: NewDeck) {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) {
    throw new Error('Unauthorized');
  }
  // ... ensure data belongs to userId
}

// Server Components
export default async function DashboardPage() {
  const user = await currentUser();
  if (!user) {
    redirect('/sign-in');
  }
  // ... fetch user's data only
}
```

## Database Security Rules

### ✅ ALWAYS Filter by userId
```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Always include userId in queries
const userDecks = await db.select()
  .from(decks)
  .where(eq(decks.userId, userId));

// ✅ GOOD - Verify ownership before operations
const deck = await db.select()
  .from(decks)
  .where(and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.userId, userId)));

if (!deck.length) {
  throw new Error('Deck not found or access denied');
}

// ✅ GOOD - Cards access through deck ownership
const userCards = await db.select()
  .from(cards)
  .innerJoin(decks, eq(cards.deckId, decks.id))
  .where(eq(decks.userId, userId));
```

### ❌ NEVER Access Data Without User Filtering
```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Missing userId filter
const allDecks = await db.select().from(decks);

// ❌ BAD - Using only ID without ownership check
const deck = await db.select()
  .from(decks)
  .where(eq(decks.id, deckId));

// ❌ BAD - Direct card access without deck ownership
const card = await db.select()
  .from(cards)
  .where(eq(cards.id, cardId));
```

## API Route Security

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Protected API route pattern
export async function GET(request: Request) {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) {
    return Response.json({ error: 'Unauthorized' }, { status: 401 });
  }

  try {
    const userDecks = await db.select()
      .from(decks)
      .where(eq(decks.userId, userId))
      .orderBy(desc(decks.createdAt));

    return Response.json({ decks: userDecks });
  } catch (error) {
    return Response.json({ error: 'Internal server error' }, { status: 500 });
  }
}

// ✅ GOOD - Update with ownership verification
export async function PATCH(
  request: Request,
  { params }: { params: { id: string } }
) {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) {
    return Response.json({ error: 'Unauthorized' }, { status: 401 });
  }

  // Verify ownership before update
  const [deck] = await db.select()
    .from(decks)
    .where(and(eq(decks.id, params.id), eq(decks.userId, userId)));

  if (!deck) {
    return Response.json({ error: 'Deck not found' }, { status: 404 });
  }

  // Now safe to update
  const updatedDeck = await db.update(decks)
    .set({ title: 'New Title', updatedAt: new Date() })
    .where(eq(decks.id, params.id))
    .returning();

  return Response.json({ deck: updatedDeck[0] });
}
```

## Server Actions Security

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Protected server action
export async function createDeck(formData: FormData) {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) {
    throw new Error('Unauthorized');
  }

  const title = formData.get('title') as string;
  
  const [newDeck] = await db.insert(decks)
    .values({
      title,
      userId, // Always set userId
    })
    .returning();

  revalidatePath('/dashboard');
  return { success: true, deck: newDeck };
}

// ✅ GOOD - Delete with ownership check
export async function deleteDeck(deckId: string) {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) {
    throw new Error('Unauthorized');
  }

  // Verify ownership
  const [deck] = await db.select()
    .from(decks)
    .where(and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.userId, userId)));

  if (!deck) {
    throw new Error('Deck not found or access denied');
  }

  await db.delete(decks).where(eq(decks.id, deckId));
  revalidatePath('/dashboard');
}
```

## Critical Security Checklist

- [ ] Every API route checks `auth()` for `userId`
- [ ] Every database query includes `userId` in WHERE clause
- [ ] Ownership verification before UPDATE/DELETE operations
- [ ] Cards accessed only through owned decks
- [ ] Server actions validate user authentication
- [ ] No raw ID-based access without ownership check
- [ ] Return 401 for unauthenticated requests
- [ ] Return 404 for unauthorized resource access

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

1. **Trusting client-side data** - Always get `userId` from Clerk's `auth()`
2. **Missing ownership checks** - Verify user owns resource before operations
3. **Direct card access** - Cards should be accessed through deck ownership
4. **Forgetting userId in inserts** - Always set `userId` when creating records
5. **Inconsistent error handling** - Use 401 for auth, 404 for not found/unauthorized